# MoodLab full-stack mobile

## Monorepo

- **pnpm workspaces** — install from repo root; never add duplicate deps without checking workspace packages
- **Shared types** — `MoodEntry`, validation, and API contracts live in `@moodlab/shared`
- **Mobile** — `@moodlab/mobile` (Expo Router, TypeScript)
- **API** — `@moodlab/api` (Hono, in-memory store until persistence is added)

## Mobile (Expo)

- Use Expo Router file-based routing under `apps/mobile/app/`
- API calls go through `apps/mobile/lib/api.ts`; base URL from `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL`
- Prefer `FlatList` for lists; handle loading and error states
- Support light/dark via existing themed components
- Run `pnpm --filter @moodlab/mobile typecheck` after TS changes

## API (Hono)

- REST under `/api/v1/`; JSON responses as `{ data }` or `{ error }`
- Validate inputs with `@moodlab/shared` validators
- Keep handlers thin; persistence in `store.ts` (replace with DB module later)
- CORS enabled for Expo web and dev clients

## Testing

- `packages/shared` and `apps/api` use Vitest
- Add mobile tests with Jest/RTL or Maestro when features stabilize

## Skills & rules

- Mobile platform rules: `.cursor/rules/mobile-development.mdc`
- Flutter/Android/iOS agent skills: installed globally — see `docs/SKILLS.md`
